-- Australia shares end 0.5 pct up on financials, Fed; NZ near record high
-- 
-- Thu Oct 30, 2014 01:28AM EDT
-- None



SYDNEY, Oct 30 (Reuters) - Australian shares rose on Thursday, buoyed by financials and consumer stocks, as investors took heart from the Federal Reserve's optimism about the U.S. economic recovery and shrugged off a profit drop by major lender National Australia Bank <NAB.AX>. [ID:nL4N0SP1IM]

The S&P/ASX 200 index <.AXJO> ended up 0.5 percent at 5,476.2, a whisker away from a seven-week high touched Wednesday.